Labeled an aberration by the Consortium, the Recorder is not yet free. Time is running out as an engineered bioweapon wreaks havoc on friend and foe alike.

Stopping both the biological agent and the people who created it is no easy task, especially since the Recorder and her friends are trapped on a research station infested with behemoth insects. Without Consortium technology, the probability of neutralizing the threat falls to nothing. In order to save her allies, the Recorder must activate a drone, but her success might destroy any hope for freedom, a future, and a name.', 'A sci-fi tale of the Recorder, labeled an aberration, facing enemies and engineered bioweapons in a thrilling quest for freedom.', 2025, NULL, '979-8886050974', 368, NULL, 1046, 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/91KA7nvM+SL._SL1500_.jpg', '/works/OL37855154W', NULL, 'June 17, 2025', 'English', 'Enclave Publishing', 1, 0, 'guardian-cathy-mccrumb', 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-16 21:57:21', '2026-03-20T16:04:41.606Z');
